**Network Dimensioning:**
Network Dimensioning, on the other hand, deals with determining the required network resources and capacity needed to support a specific set of services, applications, or users It involves calculating the necessary bandwidth,{\#}x201F;storage, and other network components to guarantee a certain level of service quality and performance.

The main objective of network dimensioning is to identify the minimum network resources required to support a specific traffic demand, thereby preventing congestion and ensuring satisfactory network performance.

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to determine the optimal network configuration that can accommodate expected traffic volumes and patterns while maintaining the desired quality of service and performance levels.
The main objective of network dimensioning is to determine the required network infrastructure to handle anticipated traffic volumes, ensure desired levels of network performance and quality.
In essence, network dimensioning is about designing the network infrastructure to accommodate predicted traffic volumes, to provide the desired quality of service (e.g., throughput delay).
The primary objective of network dimensioning is to design a network that can handle the expected traffic load, support future growth and provide the desired quality of service (QoS).

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to determine the amount of network resources required to handle projected traffic volumes, thus ensuring the network can deliver the desired level of service quality.
The primary objective of network dimensioning is to design a network that can accommodate the expected traffic load without overloading or underutilizing its resources.
The primary objective of network dimensioning is to design a network that can handle the expected volume of traffic and provide the desired quality of service.

The main objective of network dimensioning is to design or upgrade a network to accommodate projected traffic growth, satisfy specific service level agreements SLAs), and maintain an acceptable level of performance.
The main objective of network dimensioning is to determine the required network infrastructure, configure it properly and upgrade it when necessary to handle increasing traffic volumes.

The main objective of network dimensioning is to identify the optimal network configuration to satisfy projected traffic demand, ensure a predetermined quality of service (QoS), and maintain reliability and scalability.

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to determine the optimal size of the network infrastructure needed to handle expected traffic loads, considering factors like peak usage rates, packet loss ratios, latency, and throughput requirements.

In simpler terms, dimensioning is about deciding how much network capacity you need to build into your infrastructure so that it can handle the expected amount of traffic and provide the desired level of service.

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to determine the adequate size and configuration of the network infrastructure to handle projected traffic loads, avoiding congestion, packet loss, and ensuring acceptable delays.

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to identify the minimum amount of network resources needed to accommodate expected traffic volumes and patterns, ensuring the desired levels of service quality and reliability.
The primary objective of network dimensioning is to design a network that meets the expected traffic demands while maintaining acceptable levels of performance, reliability, and quality.

The primary objective of network dimensioning is to determine the minimum resources required to satisfy a specific set of service-level agreements (SLAs), performance metrics, like throughput delay packet loss rate, jitter, and other quality-of-service (QoS) parameters).
